title: Middle school cheerleaders make “Pink Out” game a success
text:
Middle school cheerleaders make “Pink Out” game a success 0 comments 
The Shippensburg Area Middle School cheerleaders, clad in “Pink Out” T-shirts, presented a check for $3,000 to Katie Maxwell of the Pennsylvania Breast Cancer Coalition during halftime of the SAMS football game Wednesday against Northern. The sold the “Pink Out” T-shirts to raise money for the donation. Back row (left to right): Emariah Russell, Ava Lohr, Aspyn Keetch, Kylie Inners, Kaitlynn Frater, Jessica Portis, Rachel Conner, PBCC volunteer Katie Maxwell, Jaden Painter, Madalynn Collett, Paige Gettel and Carlee Sommerville. Front row (l-r): Kristina Jones, Chloe Kissinger, Reagan Swenson, Michaela Fickes and Elaina Guyer.
